abstract: More than 200 counselors and staff members who are to serve 2,500 children from poverty neighborhoods of metropolitan New York this summer at the Fresh Air Fund's 3,000-acre camping and nature center on Sharpe Reservation, Fishkill, N.Y., are undergoing a "learn-in" there.
headline_main: Fresh Air Fund Aides Training; First Campers to Arrive Friday
